From Russell Peltz Subject Re How does a pitcher get a save In article fenway writes writes For the record there are two ways that a reliever can get a save He must finish the game and either have entered the game with the tying run on base at bat or on have pitched at least three innings A pitcher may not get a win and a save in the same Close but there's a number also have entered the game with no more than a run lead and pitched at least one If a pitcher finishes a game which his team has won does not get the win and satisfies at least one of the three requirements he gets a Rusty Russell Peltz Box New Haven CT